Package com.poli.human_resources_managment_server.model

Class Employee

java.lang.Object
com.poli.human_resources_managment_server.model.Employee
public class Employee extends Object
Represents an employee in the system. This class contains details about the employee, including identification, personal information, job-related data, and status.

  • Constructor Details

    • Employee

      public Employee(Integer id, String firstName, String secondName, String email, Date birthDate, double salary, Double commission, int positionId, Integer managerId, int departmentId, boolean retired)
      Constructs a new Employee instance with the specified details.
      Parameters:
      id - The unique identifier of the employee.
      firstName - The first name of the employee.
      secondName - The second name of the employee. Can be null.
      email - The email address of the employee.
      birthDate - The birth date of the employee.
      salary - The salary of the employee.
      commission - The commission of the employee. Can be null.
      positionId - The position ID associated with the employee.
      managerId - The manager's ID of the employee. Can be null if no manager.
      departmentId - The department ID where the employee works.
      retired - The retirement status of the employee.
